sentence: Among the underlying components of the Russell 3000 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Voya Financial Inc (Symbol: VOYA), where a total of 10,896 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 1.1 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 44.1% of VOYA's average daily trading volume over the past month of 2.5 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $49 strike put option expiring March 16, 2018 , with 3,260 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 326,000 underlying shares of VOYA.

Carvana Co (Symbol: CVNA) saw options trading volume of 1,420 contracts, representing approximately 142,000 underlying shares or approximately 44% of CVNA's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 322,585 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $25 strike put option expiring March 16, 2018 , with 294 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 29,400 underlying shares of CVNA.

And Procter & Gamble Company (Symbol: PG) saw options trading volume of 54,355 contracts, representing approximately 5.4 million underlying shares or approximately 43.6% of PG's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 12.5 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $85 strike put option expiring March 16, 2018 , with 16,674 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 1.7 million underlying shares of PG.
